*** Operational Requirements
    - 1. The GPS spoof detection system shall identify GPS spoofing as it
      occurs to the aircraft GPS tracking systems while in operation.

    - 2. The GPS spoof detection system shall have a red light that allows
      users to identify if they are a target of spoofing while in operation.

    - 3. The GPS spoof detection system shall store a record of all GPS spoof
      attacks while in operation.

    - 4. The GPS spoof detection system shall be able to have data
      transferred off platform while not in operation..

    - 5. The GPS spoof detection system shall communicate with aircraft
      GPS systems while in operation.

    - 6. The GPS spoof detection system shall interface with current aircraft 
      electrical power systems while in operation.

    - 7. The GPS spoof detection system shall have dual redundancy while in operation.

    - 8. The system shall display a visual alert within 3 seconds after catching a 
      possible GPS spoof attack while in operation.

    - 9. The GPS spoof detection system shall emit a sound alert within 3 seconds 
      after catching a possible GPS spoof attack while in operation.

    - 10. The GPS spoof detection system shall have a button for the user to cancel 
      the alert while in operation

