** presentation

*** usability

**** requirements
     ,Requirement 2 and Requirement 8:,
     ^("red light that allows users to identify if they are a target of spoofing")^ and ^("visual alert within 3 seconds")^
     support usability by providing visual.

     ,Requirement 5:,
     ^("communicate with aircraft GPS systems")^
     ensures seamless integration, reducing the need for pilots to manually troubleshoot compatibility issues

     ,Requirement 8:,
     ^("visual alert within 3 seconds after detection while in operation")^
     ensures users can react promptly with visual feedback

     ,Requirement 9:,
     ^("sound alert within 3 seconds")^
     adds auditory feedback

     ,Requirement 10:,
     ^("cancel the alert while in operation")^
     adds a disable button

**** functional architecture

     ,Spoof Detection Function:, 
     The system ^continuously monitors GPS^ signals by comparing received data against excepted 
     patterns or known spoofing signatures

     ,Alert Generation Function:, 
     Upon detecting a spoof, the system triggers both visual and auditory alerts within 3 seconds.

     ,Integration Function:, 
     The system interfaces with the aircraft's GPS pulling real-time data without manual 
     input from the pilot.

     ,Output Delivery Function:, 
     The red light and sound are activated via a user interface module. The interface 
     translates detection to the pilot without intermediate steps that could complicate 
     operation.

**** physical architecture
     ,Hardware Components:, 
     The system is integrated with the existing aircraft systems, using the itercom system 
     and the mission systems displays.

     ,Power Integration:, 
     The system interfaces with aircraft electrical power systems, ensuring these alerts 
     remain operational without a separate power management.

     ,Placement and Ergonomics:, 
     The system most ^consider^ the ^cockpit layout^, ensuring they are within the pilot's 
     ^line of sight^ without adding clutter or distraction. 

**** relationships
     ,maintainability:,
     If the ^red light^ or ^speaker^ can fails, maintenance must be straightforward to 
     restore usability


**** technical documents
     ,MIL-STD-1472 (Human Engineering):,
     a ^military standard^ that establishes ^human engineering^ design criteria for equipment to
     ^optimize usability^, ^safety^, and ^human performance^.

*** Disposability
**** requirements

     ,Requirement 4:,
     ^("data transferred off platform while not in operation")^ enables data preservation or system removal post-operation,
     facilitating decommissioning.

     ,Requirement 6:,
     ^("interface with current aircraft electrical power systems while in operation")^ ensures compatibility with existing power
     sources, allowing for system disconnection without major aircraft modifications, simplifying disposal.

**** functional architecture

     ,Data Offloading Function:,
     The system includes a data transfer function to extract spoofing records before disposal to ensure data is not
     lost when they system is removed.

     ,Modular Design:,
     The interface of the system must be ^plug-and-play^, 
     allowing the system to de detached without affecting core aircraft operations.

**** physical architecture

     ,Removable Components:,
     The system uses standard connectors for power and GPS interfacing, enabling physical disconnection from the
     aircraft without structural changes.

     ,Material Considerations:,
     Disposability require the system's materials to comply with avition disposal regulations, such as recycling or
     safe waste handling.

**** relationships

     Maintainability: A maintainable design could conflict with disposability if it prioritizes repair over replacement.

     Reliability: Dual redundancy (req. 7) might increase complexity, potentially complicating disposal.

**** technical documents

     End-of-Life Plan: outlines procedures for data extraction, physical removal, and disposal of components, ensuring compliance with aviation
     and environmental standards.




